*The main board would ''appear'' to be the same used by the [[D-Link DIR-862L rev A1]]. A QCA9558 WiSoC, which this 3-stream b/g/n device is presumed to be using, :could possibly be used for both the 862L (dual-stream b/g/n) and the 863. The 863L uses two serial Flash ICs (one spot is unpopulated on the 862L), possibly 32 MB in total. :There also appears to be an unpopulated spot on the board for a NAND Flash IC.
*"21514D5500A17A1", a date code of '''1322''', a lead-free logo, and "Ver:A1" :is silkscreened on the wireless module in the FCC photos. The IC used is not shown, but it's assumed to be the same as the [[D-Link DIR-862L rev A1|862L]]'s.. :as the same board appears to be used. Two marked antennae are shown - "PCA-2825-A1" is on one, "PCA-2010-" + "A14" is on another
==Probable used PSUs== The FCC external photos show the device with either an ADS0271-W 120200 or a '''JENTEC''' CG2412-B.
